    "_scoring_notes": "Scoring: Each item is rated in a 5-point Likert scale in terms of the difficulty the patient has experienced in completing each item. A score of 1 = an inability to complete the item and a score of 5 = no difficulty experienced at all. Summative scores are generated for each domain. Domain scores range from 0-100.The Stroke Impact Scale (SIS) is scored in the following way, for each domain:Transformed Scale = [(Actual raw score - lowest possible raw score) / Possible raw score range] x 100Three items in the emotion domain, 3f, 3h, and 3i, are reverse-scored, i.e., 1 becomes 5, 2 becomes 4, 3 remains the same, 4 becomes 2, and 5 becomes 1, prior to manual calculation. For these items, use the following equation to compute the individual's score:6 - individual's rating = item scoreThe last item assesses the participant's overall perception of recovery and is presented in the form of a visual analog scale from 0 to 100, where 0 = \"no recovery\" and 100 = \"full recovery.\""
  },
  "translations": {
    "en": {
      "info_sis_820701": "Stroke Impact ScaleVERSION 3.0The purpose of this questionnaire is to evaluate how stroke has impacted your health and life. We want to know from YOUR POINT OF VIEW how stroke has affected you. We will ask you questions about impairments and disabilities caused by your stroke, as well as how stroke has affected your quality of life. Finally, we will ask you to rate how much you think you have recovered from your stroke.",
      "physical_820701": "These questions are about the physical problems which may have occurred as a result of your stroke.",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_arm": "1a.  In the past week, how would you rate the strength of your arm that was most affected by your stroke?",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_arm_opt_5": "A lot of strength",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_arm_opt_4": "Quite a bit of strength",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_arm_opt_3": "Some strength",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_arm_opt_2": "A little strength",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_arm_opt_1": "No strength at all",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_grip": "1b.  In the past week, how would you rate the strength of your grip of your hand that was most affected by your stroke?",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_grip_opt_5": "A lot of strength",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_grip_opt_4": "Quite a bit of strength",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_grip_opt_3": "Some strength",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_grip_opt_2": "A little strength",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_grip_opt_1": "No strength at all",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_leg": "1c.  In the past week, how would you rate the strength of your leg that was most affected by your stroke?",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_leg_opt_5": "A lot of strength",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_leg_opt_4": "Quite a bit of strength",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_leg_opt_3": "Some strength",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_leg_opt_2": "A little strength",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_leg_opt_1": "No strength at all",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_foot_ankle": "1d.  In the past week, how would you rate the strength of your foot/ankle that was most affected by your stroke?",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_foot_ankle_opt_5": "A lot of strength",
      "functionalityafterstrokeadult_strength_past7days_foot_ankle_opt_4": "Quite a bit of strength",
